I"P<p>Cablegram 496 CANBERRA, 15 August 1947, 11.45 a.m.</p>

<p>MOST IMMEDIATE TOP SECRET PERSONAL</p>

<p>I have received your telegram and note you are resigning tomorrow.</p>

<p>Your resignation is accepted. I regret that you have not been able to carry on with the work you have been endeavouring to do under difficult circumstances.</p>

<p>In the public interest, as well as your own, any controversy or unnecessary statements regarding your resignation can only do harm. I would be obliged if you could see me after your return.</p>

<p>_</p>

<p>_</p>

